        <exercise id="fs-id3408317" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1429214">    <para id="import-auto-id1435891">You can chew through very tough objects with your incisors because they exert a large force on the small area of a pointed tooth. What pressure in pascals can you create by exerting a force of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>500 N</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> with your tooth on an area of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>mm</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>?</para></problem></exercise>
